  "source": "gemini",
  "raw_text": "Writing in reverse is a constructivist inquiry model that reverses the traditional linear rationalist flow. Traditional flow is thesis to support to conclusion. Writing in reverse flow is final learning supported by sequential reverse evidence back to first inquiry. A conclusion is a static synthesis that attempts to halt thought. A final learning is a dynamic synthesis that acts as the highest-ranked temporary solution which immediately becomes the platform for the next inquiry. Reverse structure leverages sense over rationale. Reader is told the destination first then shown the trail that led there confirming the journey by anchoring every piece of support to the validated outcome. It validates the process of discovery not just the final intellectual property.",
